# Descriptive analysis 

Generate a summary table showing the mean, standard deviation, and number of reviews for each combination of site and airline.


::: {#tbl-descriptive .cell}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
#| label: tbl-descriptive
#| fig-alt: "Descriptive Statistics of Review Scores by Site (Tripadvisor, Skytrax) and Airline (LCC:Ryanair, FCC:Lufthansa)"
descriptive_table <- airline_data %>%
  group_by(site, airline) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_score = mean(score, na.rm = TRUE),
    sd_score = sd(score, na.rm = TRUE),
    n_reviews = n()
  )
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr .hidden}

```
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'site'. You can override using the
`.groups` argument.
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
#| label: tbl-descriptive
#| fig-alt: "Descriptive Statistics of Review Scores by Site (Tripadvisor, Skytrax) and Airline (LCC:Ryanair, FCC:Lufthansa)"
descriptive_table %>%
  gt() %>%
  tab_header(
    title = "Descriptive Statistics of Review Scores by Site and Airline"
  ) %>%
  fmt_number(
    columns = vars(mean_score, sd_score),
    decimals = 2
  )
```

